==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Formalist
<hw>Form"al*ist</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>formaliste</ets>.]</ety> <def>One overattentive to forms, or too
much confined to them; esp., one who rests in external religious forms,
or observes strictly the outward forms of worship, without possessing
the life and spirit of religion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>As far a <qex>formalist</qex> from wisdom sits,⟦br⟧
In judging eyes, as libertines from wits.</q>
<rj><qau>Young.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Formality</ent>⟦br⟧
